## My Philosophy

**"2x knowledge for x/2 time"** — To live with better freedom, have twice the knowledge for the work you're executing. This lets you complete tasks in half the time and reclaim your freedom.

**Currently reading** to build this depth:
- Designing Data-Intensive Applications (Martin Kleppmann)
- Database Internals (Alex Petrov)
- CMU 15-445/645 course (Andy Pavlo)

**On learning**: Reading is easy; it's the tech jargon that creates fear. As a newbie, I ask a lot of questions — often because concepts build on assumed knowledge. I want to document these questions and learnings to help others in the same position.

**On expression**: Coming from a middle-class Indian background, I've noticed we often replace genuine understanding with textbook definitions to chase grades. I'm working to change this — to express ideas in my own words, not regurgitated definitions.

